definition: to fix/to settle/to wangle
to do/to make/to go in for/to set up/to get hold of/to take care of
to set/to fix/to determine/to decide/to order

sentences.english: You shouldn't have to do those things, the phone should just work.
sentences.chinese: 你沒必要做那些事情，那是手機本身就應該搞定的。

sentences.english: Hiya, Rog. Frank, you all set?
sentences.chinese: 嗨，你好，羅格。佛蘭克，你都搞定了嗎？

sentences.english: I don’t know if that’s finished or not yet. I hope so.
sentences.chinese: 我也不知道搞沒搞定呢，但願都沒問題了吧。
她搞定我了，就像催眠一樣。

sentences.english: Simply keep practicing the Windsor Knot a few more times until you can tie this necktie knot within less than two minutes.
sentences.chinese: 你可以多練練溫莎結的打法，爭取兩分鐘就能搞定它。

sentences.english: However, Sir Alex has faith that a conlusion will soon be reached.
sentences.chinese: 但是福格森爵士很有信心最近就搞定一切。

sentences.english: Let me ask some questions, which might help you sort it out.
sentences.chinese: 我現在問你幾個問題，也許能幫助你搞定它。

sentences.english: Doing so will pay off handsomely in the end.
sentences.chinese: 這樣做最終將讓您漂亮地搞定一切。

sentences.english: Side-seam pockets, buttoned coin pocket at the right hip.
sentences.chinese: 側縫口袋，右髖搞定硬幣口袋。

sentences.english: I finished it in one day!
Don Nelson and I just turned this thing around, didn't we, Nellie?Nellie?
sentences.chinese: 尼爾森和我只是想搞定這件事情而已，對吧，尼爾森？

sentences.english: I'm hoping it can all be done before I go away on holiday.
sentences.chinese: 在去渡假之前，我希望能把這件事全搞定。

sentences.english: Just ask a girlfriend to “gently” remind you of your intention by giving you a once-a-day call.
sentences.chinese: 讓你的女朋友每天大個電話溫柔地提醒你就搞定了。

sentences.english: Ha ha, however I made out the menu of the dinner on new year's eve with my parents yesterday.
sentences.chinese: 呵呵，昨天還是纏着他們把年夜飯的菜譜搞定了。
好吧，讓我們來搞定這事。

sentences.english: "Sonya" claims to have managed two such routes.
sentences.chinese: “索尼婭”聲稱搞定過兩條這樣的路線。
